		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Restrictions on Transfer</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Pursuant to the Digital Asset Purchase and Sale Agreement, the Initial Purchased Digital Assets (approximately 45% of the Company&#x2019;s SUI holdings) are subject to a lock<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-up</FONT> period of thirty (30)&#x00a0;days after the two<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-year</FONT> anniversary of the closing date of the PIPE Transaction. The Initial Purchase Digital Assets may be used in the Company&#x2019;s staking activity, subject to the Sui Foundation&#x2019;s approval.</P>
		 <P STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;"></P>
	</DIV>

		<P CLASS="LRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">31</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>



	<DIV CLASS="Basic-Text-Frame" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;">
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Financing Strategy</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Our Board and management have been examining potential uses of cash and have determined that investing in SUI is currently the best use of our cash. SUI will be our principal treasury holding on an ongoing basis, subject to market conditions and our anticipated cash needs. As we embark on our new treasury policy and strategy, our Board intends to proactively evaluate our use of cash, ensuring we maintain adequate working capital.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">We view SUI as our core holding and expect to continue to accumulate SUI.&#x00a0;We have not set any specific target for the amount of SUI we seek to hold, and we will continue to monitor market conditions in determining whether to engage in financings to purchase additional SUI.&#x00a0;This overall strategy also contemplates that we may (i)&#x00a0;periodically sell SUI for general corporate purposes, including to generate cash for treasury management, for acquisitions, or for strategies that generate tax benefits in accordance with applicable law, and (ii)&#x00a0;pursue strategies to create income streams or otherwise generate funds using our SUI holdings.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">At this time, we do not have a specific policy governing the percentage of our treasury holdings that will be SUI.&#x00a0;As of August 26, 2025, we held an aggregate 96,318,536 SUI, or approximately 81% of our treasury, which we acquired for an aggregate purchase price of approximately $350.8 million, inclusive of fees and expenses.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Hedging</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The Company currently does not engage in derivative or hedging transactions. In the event the Company engages in derivative or hedging transactions in the future, it will notify investors via a prospectus supplement, current report on Form&#x00a0;8<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-K</FONT> or annual or quarterly reports, as applicable, and/or on the Company&#x2019;s website.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Policies Related to Air Drops, Incidental Rights and Hard Forks</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Airdrops:&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT>Airdrops refer to the distribution of digital assets to holders of an existing cryptocurrency, typically for promotional or network development purposes. The promotors of a new digital asset announce to holders of another digital asset that such holders will be entitled to claim a certain amount of the new digital asset for free, based on the fact that they hold such other digital asset. Airdrops may be conducted by sending a token to the holders of set amounts of SUI.&#x00a0;Alternatively, airdrops may involve a user being entitled to claim tokens on a decentralized application, second<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-layer</FONT> network or entirely separate digital asset network. As such, a user entitled to receive airdrops may be required to take little or significant actions in order to receive such airdropped tokens. The Company intends to evaluate each airdrop on a case<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-by</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-case</FONT> basis, together with the Asset Manager (Galaxy Digital Capital Management LP) and in consultation with the Company&#x2019;s legal and compliance advisors, in order to assess the asset&#x2019;s legitimacy, market viability and regulatory implications. We may choose to accept, hold, sell or distribute airdropped assets based on their alignment with our financial objectives, regulatory compliance requirements and operational capabilities, subject to internal governance procedures.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Incidental Rights</FONT>:&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;Incidental rights may arise when holders of a digital asset are granted additional privileges, such as voting rights, access to new tokens or other benefits associated with a blockchain protocol. The Company intends to review any incidental rights associated with our digital asset holdings to determine their economic and strategic value. If such rights are deemed material, we will disclose their receipt and our intended actions (e.g., exercising, transferring or declining such rights) in accordance with applicable securities laws and other applicable requirements. Decisions regarding incidental rights are made by our treasury team, with oversight from our Audit Committee to ensure compliance with corporate governance standards.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Hard Forks:&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT>A hard fork occurs when a blockchain protocol undergoes a significant change, resulting in a divergence that may create a new digital asset. In the event of a hard fork affecting our digital asset holdings, we will assess the resulting assets&#x2019; technical stability, market acceptance and regulatory status. The Board, together with the Asset Manager, in collaboration with the Company&#x2019;s legal and compliance advisors, will determine whether to claim, hold or dispose of any new assets created by the hard fork. We aim to act in the best interests of our shareholders, balancing potential financial opportunities with risks related to market volatility, regulatory uncertainty and operational complexity. Any material actions taken in response to a hard fork will be disclosed promptly to investors, including through timely press releases and regulatory filings, as required.</P>
		 <P STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;"></P>
	</DIV>

		<P CLASS="RRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">32</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>



	<DIV CLASS="_idGenObjectStyleOverride-1" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-width:0pt;">
		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Digital Asset Purchase and Sale Agreement</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">On July&#x00a0;27, 2025, the Company entered into a Digital Asset Purchase and Sale Agreement (the &#x201c;Digital Asset Purchase and Sale Agreement&#x201d;) with the Sui Foundation (the &#x201c;Foundation Investor&#x201d;), pursuant to which the Company agreed to purchase and the Foundation Investor agreed to sell and transfer certain SUI tokens as set forth in one or more confirmations. The USD price per SUI token purchased pursuant to the Digital Asset Purchase and Sale Agreement will be equal to the product of (i)&#x00a0;0.85 multiplied by (ii)&#x00a0;the twenty four (24)<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-hour</FONT> time weighted average price on the Closing Date (as defined in the Securities Purchase Agreements), as reasonably calculated by the Company. Pursuant to the terms of the Digital Asset Purchase and Sale Agreement, the SUI tokens purchased will be subject to transfer restrictions for a period of two&#x00a0;years following purchase. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the transfer restrictions will not apply to the extent necessary to enable the Company to comply, or to be in compliance with, the provisions of the U.S.&#x00a0;Investment Company Act&#x00a0;of&#x00a0;1940. The Digital Asset Purchase and Sale Agreement also provides the Company with certain preemptive rights to purchase additional SUI tokens for a two (2)&#x00a0;year period after the Closing Date.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Custody of the Company&#x2019;s SUI Holdings</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">On July&#x00a0;26, 2025, the Company and BitGo Trust Company, Inc. (&#x201c;BitGo&#x201d;) entered into a Custodial Services Agreement (the &#x201c;Custodial Agreement&#x201d;) under which BitGo safeguards the private keys and crypto assets that the Company deposits with it. BitGo&#x2019;s custodial accounts are segregated and secure, and BitGo carries insurance policies that may cover certain losses. BitGo is a qualified custodian regulated by the South Dakota Division of Banking, which provides assurance that our custodied assets are held in a compliant manner.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">As a regulated custodian, BitGo is subject to a detailed statutory and regulatory framework, including holding customer assets in segregated client accounts on behalf of customers. 100% of Trust assets and private keys safekeeped by BitGo will be held in cold storage in segregated accounts and are never commingled with BitGo or other client assets. BitGo applies industry standards, such as CryptoCurrency Security Standard (CCSS) and SOC1 and SOC2, while also working with the most trusted brands in the industry and offering clients comprehensive insurance solutions.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The BitGo ecosystem and architecture for private key management include the BitGo Platform, hardware security modules (&#x201c;HSMs&#x201d;) and modular services. The BitGo cold custody solution is built on BitGo&#x2019;s security to manage keys on behalf of customers. BitGo only signs transactions that have been authorized by the Sponsor and follow the policies set by the account administrators.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The primary keys and backup keys are created offline using an Offline Vault Console (&#x201c;OVC&#x201d;) on air gapped laptops during a secure ceremony to create hardened cryptographic seeds that power the BitGo solution. This is to ensure only machines which have no access to the internet and are pristine are able to see private key material.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Undisclosed personnel at BitGo hold the sharded keys. When they are reconstituted, they are able to sign a transaction which moves funds in the public blockchain. To mitigate collusion, the individuals who have the sharded keys are different from those who have access to the vaults where the signings happen.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The private key is reconstituted in the OVC, but only in internal memory. At no point is it displayed or shown to any user. After signing is done, the key is no longer available in memory. The OVC is run in a read<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-only</FONT> disk, so once the laptop is powered off, there is no non<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-volatile</FONT> storage of any kind to write back to disk. The OVC operates using a RAM disk, where it simulates a real hard disk, but it is completely ephemeral and is wiped as soon as the machine is power cycled or rebooted, thus wiping the reconstituted private key and preventing it from being copied or compromised.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">BitGo is a South Dakota trust company and the private keys are strategically distributed across various geographic locations within the United&#x00a0;States. In order to enhance security measures, BitGo refrains from disclosing the exact locations of these keys.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">At time of wallet creation, BitGo creates a unique key pair within its HSM in order to give each client a unique wallet on<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT>. These online keys are wrapped by the BitGo HSM and stored within BitGo&#x2019;s data vault for the BitGo Platform keys used to sign transactions.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">As all custody wallets are segregated, the existence of SUI held by the Company can be verified on<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT> by the Company or any other authorized party.</P>
		 <P STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;"></P>
	</DIV>

		<P CLASS="LRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">33</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>



	<DIV CLASS="_idGenObjectStyleOverride-1" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-width:0pt;">
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">BitGo cold wallets are supported by a $250&#x00a0;million insurance policy issued by Lloyd&#x2019;s of London. The specifics of the policy include Cyber Insurance, E&amp;O, general specie. Any copying and theft of private keys, insider theft or dishonest acts by BitGo employees or executives, and loss of keys directly related to BitGo&#x2019;s custody of keys would be covered by this amount at minimum. This insurance policy is shared among all of BitGo&#x2019;s clients and is not specific to the Trust or to customers holding bitcoin and may not be available or sufficient to protect the Trust from all possible losses or sources of losses. The Company may purchase additional insurance coverage through BitGo&#x2019;s underwriter, though the Company has not purchased such additional insurance cover as of the date of this prospectus. BitGo is not FDIC<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-insured</FONT>. BitGo has established a business continuity plan that will support its ability to conduct business in the event of a significant business disruption. This plan is reviewed and updated annually, and can be updated more frequently, if deemed necessary, by BitGo in its sole discretion. Should BitGo be impacted by a significant business disruption, BitGo aims to minimize business interruption as quickly and efficiently as possible.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The Custodial Agreement commenced on the effective date, as detailed in the agreement, and will continue for one (1)&#x00a0;year, unless earlier terminated in accordance with the terms of the Custodial Agreement. After the initial term, the Custodial Agreement will automatically renew for one<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-year</FONT> successive renewal terms, unless either party notifies the other of its intention not to renew with at least 60&#x00a0;days&#x2019; prior<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-notice</FONT>. Either party may terminate the Custodial Agreement for a material breach if such breach is not cured within 30&#x00a0;days following written notice thereof. BitGo may suspend or restrict the Company&#x2019;s access to the custodial services and/or deactivate, terminate or cancel the Company&#x2019;s custodial account for any reason upon providing at least thirty (30)&#x00a0;days&#x2019; written notice to the Company, or immediately if BitGo perceives a risk of legal or regulatory non<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-compliance</FONT> associated with the Company&#x2019;s custodial account activity, among other things. The Company may terminate the Custodial Agreement at any time upon providing at least 30&#x00a0;days&#x2019; written notice to BitGo, paying outstanding amounts and an early termination fee.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">SUI, SUI Markets and Regulation of SUI</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">This section provides a more detailed description of SUI, including information about the historical development of SUI, how a person holds SUI, how to use SUI in transactions, how to trade SUI, the spot markets where SUI can be bought, held and sold, the SUI OTC market and SUI validating.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">SUI and the Sui Network</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">SUI is a digital asset that is created and transmitted through the operations of the peer<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-to</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-peer</FONT> Sui Network, a network of computers that operates on cryptographic protocols. No single entity owns or operates the Sui Network, the infrastructure of which is collectively maintained by a broad user base. The Sui Network allows people to exchange tokens of value, called SUI, which are recorded on a public transaction ledger known as a blockchain. SUI can be used to pay for transaction fees and network operations, including computational power on the Sui Network, or it can be converted to fiat currencies, such as the U.S.&#x00a0;dollar, at rates determined on digital asset trading platforms or in individual end<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-user</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">to-end</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-user</FONT> transactions under a barter system. Furthermore, the Sui Network was designed to allow users to write and implement smart contracts&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;that is, general<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-purpose</FONT> code that executes on the network and can instruct the transmission of information and value based on a sophisticated set of logical conditions. Using smart contracts, users can create markets, store registries of debts or promises, represent the ownership of property, move funds in accordance with conditional instructions and create digital assets other than SUI on the Sui Network. Smart contract operations are executed on the Sui blockchain in exchange for payment of SUI.&#x00a0;Like the Ethereum network, the Sui Network is one of a number of projects intended to expand blockchain use beyond just a peer<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-to</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-peer</FONT> money system.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The Sui Network primarily uses a delegated proof<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-of</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-stake</FONT> consensus mechanism to incentivize SUI holders to validate transactions. Unlike proof<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-of</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-work</FONT>, in which miners expend computational resources to compete to validate transactions and are rewarded coins in proportion to the amount of computational resources expended, in proof<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-of</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-stake</FONT>, validators risk or &#x201c;stake&#x201d; coins to compete to be randomly selected to validate transactions and are rewarded coins in proportion to the amount of coins staked. Any malicious activity, such as disagreeing with the eventual consensus or otherwise violating protocol rules, results in the forfeiture or &#x201c;slashing&#x201d; of a portion of the staked coins. Proof<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-of</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-stake</FONT> is viewed as more energy efficient and scalable than proof<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-of</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-work</FONT>.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Unlike many other smart contract platforms that batch transaction into blocks, Sui validators individually validate transactions. Sui uses &#x201c;Narwhal&#x201d; and &#x201c;Bullshark&#x201d; as its memory pool and consensus engines, respectively, which supplement proof<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-of</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-stake</FONT> by allowing transactions performed on Sui to be verified and executed in parallel, rather than sequentially like in prominent blockchains like Bitcoin and Ethereum. Under Narwhal, instead of a proposing </P>
		 <P STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;"></P>
	</DIV>

		<P CLASS="RRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">34</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>



	<DIV CLASS="_idGenObjectStyleOverride-1" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-width:0pt;">
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">validator broadcasting all transactions in a block to the other validators, the proposing validators send references to transactions that other validators have already received in their local memory pools. These memory pools serve as logs of unprocessed transactions awaiting verification and execution on a blockchain. The transaction data can thus bypass the full consensus process, removing the large data transmission step which often impedes proof<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-of</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-stake</FONT> consensus and introduces latency. Further unlike traditional blockchains, which add transactions in a single, linear sequence, Bullshark uses a structure whereby each transaction points to multiple previous transactions, allowing many transactions to be processed at the same time. The purpose of Narwhal and Bullshark is to increase scalability of a blockchain allowing for parallel processing of transactions and increasing transaction speed.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Founding</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The Sui Network was initially conceived in 2021 by Evan Cheng, Adeniyi Abiodun, Sam Blackshear, George Danezis, and Kostas Chalkias to continue research initially performed while the group was employed by Meta Platforms, Inc., in which they collaborated on a digital asset project called Diem (formerly known as Libra). Mysten Labs Inc. (&#x201c;Mysten&#x201d;), an independent consortium of blockchain software developers which contributes to the development of the Sui Network, formed as an outgrowth of the Diem project. The Sui Foundation is an independent nonprofit entity that supports research and development of open<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-source</FONT> technology related to Sui.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Although Mysten and the Sui Foundation continue to exert significant influence over the direction of the development of SUI, the Sui Network is distributed and does not require governmental authorities or financial institution intermediaries to create, transmit or determine the value of SUI.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Technology and Operation</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Parallel Execution and </FONT><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Object-Centric</FONT><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;"> Model</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Unlike traditional blockchain models that rely on sequential transaction execution, SUI&#x2019;s architecture enables parallel transaction execution, significantly increasing throughput. Transactions involving independent objects can be processed simultaneously, reducing bottlenecks. The object<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-centric</FONT> model provides a more intuitive and developer<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-friendly</FONT> way to structure smart contracts. Each object has a defined owner, allowing SUI to optimize state management and computation.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Narwhal and Bullshark Consensus Mechanism</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The Sui Network employs a dual<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-layer</FONT> consensus mechanism known as Narwhal and Bullshark, which decouples transaction ordering from execution. Narwhal is a key component of the Sui Network&#x2019;s consensus mechanism. It is a high<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-performance</FONT> memory pool that organizes transactions into a Directed Acyclic Graph (&#x201c;DAG&#x201d;) structure. This organization allows for efficient transaction processing and reduces the likelihood of bottlenecks. Narwhal&#x2019;s design ensures that the Sui Network can maintain high throughput and low latency, making it suitable for applications that require rapid transaction processing.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Bullshark is the consensus protocol used by the Sui Network, built on top of Narwhal. It is designed to achieve fast finality and high security. Bullshark uses a byzantine fault tolerant consensus mechanism, which ensures that the network can reach consensus even in the presence of malicious actors. This protocol is optimized for performance, allowing the Sui Network to process a large number of TPS while maintaining a high level of security.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Smart Contracts and Development on the Sui Network</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Smart contracts are programs that run on a blockchain that can execute automatically when certain conditions are met. Smart contracts facilitate the exchange of anything representative of value, such as money, information, property, or voting rights. Using smart contracts, users can send or receive digital assets, create markets, store registries of debt or promises represent ownership of property or a company, move funds in accordance with conditional instructions and create new digital assets.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Development on the Sui Network involves building more complex tools on top of smart contracts, such as decentralized apps and organizations that are autonomous, known as decentralized autonomous organizations; and entirely new decentralized networks. For example, a company that distributes charitable donations on behalf of users could hold donated funds in smart contracts that are paid to charities only if the charity satisfies certain pre<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-defined</FONT> conditions.</P>
		 <P STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;"></P>
	</DIV>

		<P CLASS="LRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">35</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>



	<DIV CLASS="_idGenObjectStyleOverride-1" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-width:0pt;">
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">In total, as of June&#x00a0;2024, more than 86 apps are currently built on the Sui Network, including in the collectible NFT, gaming, music streaming, and decentralized finance categories.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Additionally, the Sui Network has been used for DeFI platforms, which seek to democratize access to financial services, such as borrowing, lending, custody, trading, derivatives and insurance, by removing third<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-party</FONT> intermediaries. DeFi can allow users to lend and earn interest on their digital assets, exchange one digital asset for another and create derivative digital assets such as stablecoins, which are digital assets pegged to a reserve asset such as fiat currency.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Unlike native fungible tokens, which are primarily used for payments and transaction fees, NFTs represent ownership of unique digital or real<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-world</FONT> assets. On the Sui Network, NFTs can encode rights to in<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-game</FONT> assets, digital art, music, or utility tokens within applications. NFTs are tradable across applications, contributing to a new, internet<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-native</FONT> economy. This new paradigm allows users to own rights to other assets through NFTs, which enable users to trade them with others on the Sui Network. For example, an NFT may convey rights to a digital asset that exists in an online game or a decentralized app, and users can trade their NFT in the decentralized app or game, and carry them to other digital experiences, creating an entirely new free<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-market</FONT> internet<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-native</FONT> economy that can be monetized in the physical world.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Overview of the Sui Network&#x2019;s Operations</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">In order to own, transfer or use SUI directly on the Sui Network (as opposed to through an intermediary, such as a custodian), a person generally must have internet access to connect to the Sui Network. SUI transactions may be made directly between end<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-users</FONT> without the need for a third<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-party</FONT> intermediary. The Sui Network prevents double<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-spending</FONT> by validating and recording transactions either through direct validator execution or, when needed, via consensus. Transactions involving shared objects are memorialized on the Sui blockchain to ensure consistency and prevent conflicts. This verification process is managed by validators who either directly execute transactions or reach consensus to include shared<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-object</FONT> transactions in checkpointed blocks. These blocks form part of the Sui blockchain, which acts as a source of truth for shared state. Unlike traditional blockchains that rely solely on the sequential production of blocks for all transactions, the Sui Network differentiates between independent and shared transactions. Independent transactions can be executed in parallel without global ordering, while only shared transactions require consensus and block inclusion.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">SUI Token Issuance</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Initial Creation of SUI and SUI Supply</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Unlike Bitcoin, which was solely created through a progressive mining process, 10&#x00a0;billion SUI were created in connection with the launch of the Sui Network. Following the launch of the Sui Network, no further SUI will be created unless a modification (or &#x201c;fork&#x201d;) of the Sui Network&#x2019;s protocol occurs. The Sui Network&#x2019;s capped total supply of 10&#x00a0;billion SUI tokens are unlocked according to a distribution and unlock schedule designed to balance liquidity, stability, and long<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-term</FONT> growth. The current unlock schedule is subject to adjustments to ensure a stable tokenomics model that supports the Sui Network&#x2019;s health and will be available for download via an API maintained by the Sui Foundation. According to the Sui Foundation, distributions of locked SUI tokens were made to Series&#x00a0;A and Series&#x00a0;B investors and early contributors beginning in April&#x00a0;2024, and distributions of locked SUI tokens were made to Mysten Labs Treasury beginning in October&#x00a0;2023.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The Sui &#x201c;mainnet&#x201d; launched on May&#x00a0;3, 2023 with a portion of the total supply made liquid at launch. At or shortly after launch, the mainnet was supported by over 100 validators and over 400 nodes. DeepBook, the Sui Network&#x2019;s first native liquidity layer, launched in July&#x00a0;2023. This central limit order book gives DeFi protocols and other app builders a mechanism to support both market and limit token swaps. By mid<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-July</FONT>&#x00a0;2023, the Sui Network had approximately one million active wallets, rising to approximately three million active wallets by mid<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-August</FONT>&#x00a0;2023, nine million active wallets by the end of November&#x00a0;2023, and over 120&#x00a0;million active wallets by mid<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-April</FONT>&#x00a0;2025.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">On September&#x00a0;13, 2023, zkLogin, a new primitive, launched on the Sui Network, letting builders incorporate authorization through existing credentials from providers such as Google, Facebook and Twitch. This development significantly eased the onboarding path for new Web3 users.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">By February&#x00a0;2024, DeFi protocols on the Sui Network had reached $500&#x00a0;million in total value locked, putting the Sui Network in the top ten blockchains by that metric. That number rose to $1&#x00a0;billion in total value locked by the end of September&#x00a0;2024, and $2&#x00a0;billion in January&#x00a0;2025. By April&#x00a0;2024, the beta version of the 2024 edition of the Move </P>
		 <P STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;"></P>
	</DIV>

		<P CLASS="RRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">36</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>



	<DIV CLASS="_idGenObjectStyleOverride-1" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-width:0pt;">
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">programming language became available, which added many useful new features, including method syntax, positional fields, and loop labels. On June&#x00a0;18, 2024, Mysten Labs announced the launch of Walrus, a decentralized data storage network that uses SUI as a coordination layer. Walrus launched on the Sui Network in April&#x00a0;2025.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">On August&#x00a0;6, 2024, engineers launched Mysticeti, a new consensus mechanism for the Sui Network that could allow the Sui Network to process shared object transactions with even less latency. In September&#x00a0;2024, Agora&#x2019;s U.S.&#x00a0;dollar<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-backed</FONT> stablecoin arrived on the Sui Network, giving DeFi users a new option for token purchases and swaps. The advent of AUSD on the Sui Network, which was previously launched on Ethereum and Avalanche, was one of a number of native stablecoins on the Sui Network. Sui USDC, which is the SUI<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-native</FONT> version of USDC, another stablecoin, was added to the Sui Network in October&#x00a0;2024, and FDUSD, yet another stablecoin, was added to the Sui Network in November&#x00a0;2024.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The SUI token serves four purposes on the Sui Network. First, SUI can be staked within an &#x201c;epoch&#x201d; in order to participate in the proof<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-of</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-stake</FONT> mechanism. Second, SUI is the asset denomination needed for paying the Gas Fees to execute transactions or other operations on the Sui Network. Third, SUI can be used as a versatile and liquid asset for various applications including the standard features of money&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;a unit of account, a medium of exchange, or a store of value&#x00a0;&#x2014;&#x00a0;and more complex functionality enabled by smart contracts, interoperability, and composability across the Sui ecosystem. Fourth, and finally, SUI plays an important role in governance by acting as a right to participate in on<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT> voting on issues such as protocol upgrades.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The SUI token powers a variety of real<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-world</FONT> applications:</P>
		 <P CLASS="NL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">1.<FONT STYLE="width: 20px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Decentralized Finance</FONT>:&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;Lending and borrowing protocols allow users to supply SUI for interest or borrow against collateral. Yield farming and staking rewards allow liquidity providers to earn yield by participating in automated market makers and liquidity pools. Stablecoins and payments benefit from SUI&#x2019;s fast and low<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-cost</FONT> transactions, making it ideal for cross<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-border</FONT> transfers and remittances.</P>
		 <P CLASS="NL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">2.<FONT STYLE="width: 20px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Non</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">-Fungible</FONT></FONT><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;"> Tokens</FONT>:&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;NFT minting and trading allow artists and developers to create and trade NFTs on SUI&#x2019;s blockchain with low minting costs. On<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT> gaming assets enable in<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-game</FONT> items, skins, and collectibles to be represented as NFTs, unlocking true ownership.</P>
		 <P CLASS="NL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">3.<FONT STYLE="width: 20px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Gaming and Metaverse</FONT>:&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;Play<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-to</FONT><FONT CLASS="nobreak">-earn</FONT> gaming economies allow players to earn rewards in a decentralized manner. Low<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-latency</FONT> transactions enable smooth in<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-game</FONT> purchases and seamless on<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-chain</FONT> interactions.</P>
		 <P CLASS="NL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">4.<FONT STYLE="width: 20px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Supply Chain and Enterprise Solutions</FONT>:&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;Provenance and authentication solutions track goods transparently, ensuring authenticity and reducing fraud. Enterprise blockchain integration supports identity management, record<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-keeping</FONT>, and automation.</P>
		 <P CLASS="NL_m" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:48pt;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:-24pt;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">5.<FONT STYLE="width: 20px;display: inline-block;">&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;</FONT><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Identity Verification and Security</FONT>:&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;&#x00a0;Decentralized identity solutions verify credentials and prevent fraud. Data privacy enhancements allow privacy<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-preserving</FONT> transactions and selective disclosure mechanisms.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H4" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:1;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Italic" STYLE="font-style:italic;font-weight:normal;">Limits on SUI Supply</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">SUI has a fixed total supply of 10&#x00a0;billion tokens, meaning no additional SUI will be minted beyond this limit. At network launch, a portion of the total supply was in circulation, while the remaining tokens are being released progressively over time. The structured emission schedule is designed to support network security, incentivize validators and participants, and sustain the long<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-term</FONT> growth of the Sui Network.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Governance of the Sui Network and Modifications to the Protocol</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">SUI token holders participate in network governance by voting on protocol upgrades, fee adjustments, and validator policies and incentives. The governance model is designed to be inclusive and transparent, encouraging community<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-driven</FONT> decision<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-making</FONT>.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The Sui Foundation oversees ecosystem development, distributing funds for grants, research, and innovation to drive network growth. The Sui Foundation is an independent, non<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-profit</FONT> entity established to support and advance the adoption, security, and sustainability of the Sui Network. The Sui Foundation is dedicated to fostering an open ecosystem that empowers developers, users, and enterprises to build and interact with blockchain<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-based</FONT> applications. As the primary steward of the Sui Network, it plays a pivotal role in the protocol&#x2019;s long<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-term</FONT> development by overseeing ecosystem </P>
		 <P STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;"></P>
	</DIV>

		<P CLASS="LRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">37</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>



	<DIV CLASS="_idGenObjectStyleOverride-1" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-width:0pt;">
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">growth, allocating community resources, funding research initiatives, and ensuring governance transparency. The Sui Foundation operates in alignment with the principles of decentralization, innovation, and inclusivity, promoting an equitable and sustainable blockchain ecosystem.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The core development team behind the Sui Network is Mysten, a blockchain technology company focused on developing innovative and scalable solutions to enhance decentralized applications and blockchain infrastructure. Mysten played a foundational role in designing and launching the Sui Network. The company continues to contribute to SUI&#x2019;s technical advancements while fostering an ecosystem of developers, enterprises, and users who leverage its cutting<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-edge</FONT> infrastructure. Mysten operates as a private technology company and is distinct from the Sui Foundation, which oversees governance, community funding, and decentralization efforts for the Sui Network. While Mysten remains a significant contributor, the long<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-term</FONT> evolution of SUI is guided by decentralized governance mechanisms and community participation.</P>
		 <P CLASS="H2" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:12pt;orphans:99;page-break-after:avoid;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin-top:12pt;"><FONT CLASS="Bold" STYLE="font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;">Summary of a SUI Transaction</FONT></P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">The following is a summary of a payment transaction of SUI on the Sui Network.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Prior to engaging in SUI transactions directly on the Sui Network, a user generally must first install on its computer or mobile device a Sui Network software program that will allow the user to generate a private and public key pair associated with a SUI address. The Sui Network software program and the SUI address also enable the user to connect to the Sui Network and transfer SUI to, and receive SUI from, other users.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Each Sui Network address, or wallet, is associated with a unique &#x201c;public key&#x201d; and &#x201c;private key&#x201d; pair. To receive SUI, the SUI recipient must provide its public key to the party initiating the transfer. This activity is analogous to a recipient for a transaction in U.S.&#x00a0;dollars providing a routing address in wire instructions to the payor so that cash may be wired to the recipient&#x2019;s account. The payor approves the transfer to the address provided by the recipient by &#x201c;signing&#x201d; a transaction that consists of the recipient&#x2019;s public key with the private key of the address from where the payor is transferring the SUI.&#x00a0;The recipient, however, does not make public or provide to the sender its related private key. Wallets that are used to store cryptographic keys can be &#x201c;hot&#x201d; or &#x201c;cold.&#x201d; A hot wallet is connected to the internet, and is thus readily available to facilitate trading, but may be more vulnerable to hacking. A cold wallet is a wallet that stores cryptographic keys offline, such as on a computer that has no internet access, a segregated piece of hardware, or a piece of paper.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Neither the recipient nor the sender reveal their private keys in a transaction, because the private key authorizes transfer of the funds in that address to other users. Therefore, if a user loses his or her private key, the user may permanently lose access to the SUI contained in the associated address. Likewise, SUI is irretrievably lost if the private key associated with them is deleted and no backup has been made. When sending SUI, a user&#x2019;s Sui Network software program must validate the transaction with the associated private key. In addition, since every computation on the Sui Network requires processing power, there is a transaction fee involved with the transfer that is paid by the payor. The resulting digitally validated transaction is sent by the user&#x2019;s Sui Network software program to the Sui Network validators to allow transaction confirmation.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Sui Network validators record and confirm transactions when they validate and add blocks of information to the Sui Blockchain. When a validator validates transactions, it creates a block, which includes data relating to (i)&#x00a0;the verification of newly submitted and accepted transactions and (ii)&#x00a0;a reference to transactions prior to the transactions is being added. The validator becomes aware of outstanding, unrecorded transactions through the data packet transmission and distribution discussed above.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Upon the addition of a block of SUI transactions, the Sui Network software program of both the spending party and the receiving party will show confirmation of the transaction on the Sui Blockchain and reflect an adjustment to the SUI balance in each party&#x2019;s Sui Network public key, completing the SUI transaction. Once a transaction is confirmed on the Sui Blockchain, it is irreversible.</P>
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">Some SUI transactions are conducted &#x201c;off<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-blockchain</FONT>&#x201d; and are therefore not recorded in the Sui Blockchain. These &#x201c;off<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-blockchain</FONT> transactions&#x201d; involve the transfer of control over, or ownership of, a specific digital wallet holding SUI or the reallocation of ownership of certain SUI in a pooled<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-ownership</FONT> digital wallet, such as a digital wallet owned by a Digital Asset Trading Platform. In contrast to on<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-blockchain</FONT> transactions, which are publicly recorded on the Sui Blockchain, information and data regarding off<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-blockchain</FONT> transactions are generally not publicly available. Therefore, </P>
		 <P STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;"></P>
	</DIV>

		<P CLASS="RRH" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:0;orphans:1;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:center;text-indent:0;widows:1;margin: 10px 0px 10px 0pt; page-break-after: always; border-bottom: 1px solid; margin-top: 10.0pt; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 10.0pt; margin-left: 0in; text-align: center; font-size: 10.0pt; font-family: TimesNewRomanPSStd-Regular; color: black;">38</P>
		<P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:left;text-indent:0;widows:2;margin-top:8pt;"><A HREF="#TOC001">Table of Contents</A></P>



	<DIV CLASS="_idGenObjectStyleOverride-1" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;border-width:0pt;">
		 <P CLASS="Text_flush" STYLE="margin:0;padding:0;border-width:0;font-family:Times New Roman PS Std, serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;margin-bottom:0;margin-left:0;margin-right:0;margin-top:8pt;orphans:2;page-break-after:auto;page-break-before:auto;text-align:justify;text-indent:0;widows:3;margin-top:8pt;">off<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-blockchain</FONT> transactions are not truly Sui transactions in that they do not involve the transfer of transaction data on the Sui Network and do not reflect a movement of SUI between addresses recorded on the Sui Network&#x2019;s blockchain. For these reasons, off<FONT CLASS="nobreak">-blockchain</FONT> transactions are subject to risks as any such transfer of SUI ownership is not protected by the protocol behind the Sui Network or recorded in, and validated through, the blockchain mechanism.</P>
